      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The current \"paralysis\" is overwhelmingly viewed as a fundamental, structural flaw inherent to the UN's design. The Security Council's architecture, which enshrines the interests of the victors of WWII, is an anachronism that cannot adapt to the multipolar world of today. Unless the veto power is fundamentally reformed, the UN will remain a forum for diplomatic posturing rather than a true global security guarantor.",
      "source": "target",
